law.catch_line: Duty of Commonwealth's attorney and county attorney to assist child sexual abuse multidisciplinary team.
law.text: Pursuant to KRS 431.600, each Commonwealth's attorney and each county attorney shall assist any child sexual abuse multidisciplinary team established in his circuit or county, unless the Prosecutors Advisory Council has voted to relieve him of this responsibility.
law.history: Created 1994 Ky. Acts ch. 264, sec. 3, effective July 15, 1994.
